  "text": "chromosome 10q25.2 represents one of the strongest genetic associations with T2D risk reported to date, and has been shown to be highly relevant across multiple populations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Furthermore, Bayesian modeling and studies leveraging the haplotypic diversity seen in populations of African ancestry have implicated rs7903146 as the causal SNP at this locus [CITATION_3] .",
